      • solve

        public boolean solve(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> cols,
                     int row)
        Recursive method that solves the n Queens problem for this instance of ChessBoard It does this by iterating through each row, starting at n and going down to 0, traversing through a shuffled list of columns to see which one works first. The columns are shuffled because if they aren't, it will find the exact same solution every time
        Parameters:
        cols - - An ArrayList of the columns that have not yet been filled
        row - the current index
        Returns:
        Boolean true if the spot is Valid, false otherwise
